Wild rice [[flour]] was mixed with crushed [[dates]], roasted and ground [[tharra]], and [[honey]] syrup to make sweet [[Bedine]] [[vauv]] treats.{{cite web| url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210730214335/https://twitter.com/TheEdVerse/status/1421224959465119745| title = TheEdVerse on Twitter| accessdate = 30-6-2022| date = 30-7-2021}}

The [[Sheaf of Wheat]] inn in the [[Cormyr]]ean town of [[Ghars]] served hot [[oyster]] and wild rice [[stew]] to its guests. While in [[Eagle's Idyll]] in [[Airspur (Chessenta)|Airspur]] of [[Chessenta]], wild rice was broiled with [[spice]]d [[shrimp]], [[green beans]], and served as a gruel.

The city of [[Velen]] on [[Tethyr]]'s [[Dragon's Head Peninsula]] had access to a wide variety of foods including wild rice. The opulent [[Blackthorn's Brew]] festhall in Velen served a big dish called the [[Pride of Velen]], which included trumpets of steaming wild rice, [[snail]]s, [[turkey]], [[onion]]s, and [[mushroom]]s.

[[Elf|Elven]] cuisine included a dish called ''[[vaervren]]'' made by sautéing certain vegetables in [[boar]] fat and then adding [[wildfowl broth]] and wild rice, cooking them together.{{Cite web/theedverse/2023-02-22 - Vaervren}}
